description:
Sad Wings of Destiny is the second album by the English heavy metal group Judas Priest, released in 1976. Sad Wings of Destiny was Judas Priest's second and final studio record made while under contract with Gull Records, an independent UK company. Despite critical acclaim, 

the band was struggling financially due to lack of support from the small label (Rob Halford and K.K. Downing would later claim that they were living in a van outside the Gull studios) Shortly after changing management, the band severed their ties with Gull and signed with Columbia Records.
